message.content: This question requires an understanding of what an ecosystem is. An ecosystem is a community of living organisms (plants, animals, and microorganisms) in conjunction with the nonliving components of their environment (air, water, and soil). Therefore, if something is in an ecosystem, it means it is in an environment where life exists. Option (A) is incorrect because if something is in an ecosystem, it is part of that ecosystem and therefore not invisible. Option (B) is incorrect because an ecosystem exists on Earth, not in a vacuum of space. Option (D) is incorrect because an ecosystem consists of natural components and does not refer to extraterrestrial life.
